<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-050-174  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 050 174.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC Week  Jan 15 1990 v6 n2 p32(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>AlphaWorks 2.0 offers enhanced search features. (Alpha SoftwareCorp introduces Works 2.0) (product announcement)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Alpha Software Corp. (product enhancement).andO;Product:   AlphaWorks 2.0 (Office automation software) (productintroduction).andO;Topic:     Integrated softwareEnhancementsProduct Introduction.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>AlphaWorks 2.0 Offers Enhanced Search FeaturesandM;Alpha Software Corp. has added powerful new retrieval features to itsAlphaWorks integrated-software package in an attempt to give users searchcapabilities that rival those offered by relational databases.andM;AlphaWorks 2.0, released last month, sports enhanced lookup capabilities thatlet users simultaneously access information from multiple databases, providedthe databases reside in memory and are written in the dBASE DBF filestructure, according to officials at the Burlington, Mass., company.andM;AlphaWorks, designed as a standalone application for the general businessuser, comprises word-processing, database-management, spreadsheet, graphicsand communications modules.andM;The latest version of the program incorporates a new &quot;search-expressionbuilder,&quot; which allows users searching for text and data to fill in templateswith examples of what the program should search for, rather than createcomplex search statements.andM;In addition, a new &quot;file viewer&quot; feature lets users view, in a pop-up window,the contents of any file before actually calling it up.andM;Other new features include user-defined menus, mouse support, added indexingfeatures, expanded terminal-emulation capabilities and, in the communicationsmodule, error-correction protocols.andM;AlphaWorks costs $195; upgrades are available for $49.andM;AlphaSoftware Corp. can be reached at (617) 229-2924.andO;</TEXT></DOC>